text:
Open Letter to the Mayor
Hello Mr. Eric Adams, have you stepped down yet?

viewof select = Inputs.select(["Yes", "No"], {label: "Select one"})







letterIntro = { 
  if(select == "No") { 
    return "Dear Mayor Adams," 
  } else { 
    return "Welcome new mayor!" 
  } 
}







It’s time to think about floods. In the past two decades alone, NYC has experienced major flooding events that have caused millions of dollars in damage, created major transportation delays, and even cost the lives of New Yorkers. It’s time to get to work and think creatively about how our city handles water.
Green roofs are part of the answer and we should be building more of them! They store rain water during storms, relieving pressure on sewer systems. And they have many additional benefits, including:

Cooling buildings and the city
Adding beautiful green space that people can enjoy
Becoming layover spots for migratory birds
